		<td><b>NES-001 Black video and no output on PIN21 and hot PPU</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey team,<br /><br />A recent NES repairer and my first post here.<br /><br />I have been collecting NES's on New Zealand's version of eBay and fixing them up. All of them have been power or cart slot related so far. I have got to one that is not outputting any video at all. I have tried pulling signal from Pin21 of the PPU as well. The biggest thing I seem to notice is that the PPU gets really hot. Is it likely that it is dead? Is there a sure fire way to confirm that it is indeed the PPU or could another component be causing it to get that hot.<br /><br />Any point in the right direction would really be helpful.<br /><br />Cheers

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


