	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NES-001 Black video and no output on PIN21 and hot PPU</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Does every game work (with sound), just there is no video output or totally no reaction?<br /><br />If the first, check with multimeter on diode test resistance between pin 21 (VIDEO) and GND/VCC (without desoldering)- might be internally shorted.<br />Some time ago I described 100% working PPU with internally broken video generating signal.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


